29/04/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Christian Schwarz-Schilling, BiH Prime Minister Nikola Spiric and two entity prime ministers -- the Federation of BiH's Nedzad Brankovic and Republika Srpska's Milorad Dodik -- agreed on Friday (April 27th) on forming a co-ordination body for Srebrenica. 
The decision was part of efforts to calm down the current controversy about the Srebrenica municipality's status and to co-ordinate steps for the economic recovery of the region. (Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 28/04/07; RTRS, Srna, OHR Sources - 27/04/07)
